<subSubSection id="B6CD877D26EC5B527B94125A3F82E595" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="DBFCD7CB8A0020883BAEFA184AAFD1FF" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">
<taxonomicName id="DF70A2CDC2000E9F83BCA8740F7548D8" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="longicuspis">Miconia longicuspis</taxonomicName>
Herzog, Feddes Repert. Nov. Sp. 7: 64. 1909. Type: Bolivia. Cordillera de Santa Cruz: Cerro 
<normalizedToken id="8FB2B7DDDD943EDC5F31A63C50B523BE" originalValue="Amboró">Amboro</normalizedToken>
, 
<normalizedToken id="F47076BE1638AFBC68E6B400DDC919B0" originalValue="Cuñucú">Cunucu</normalizedToken>
, 600-1400 m, Oct 1907, T.Herzog 326 (holotype: Z!). Not 
<taxonomicName id="C04DB5A32CC5C5C617004ED41C51F30B" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="longicuspis">
<emphasis id="354F8DB8A0C28135B4F40462956971A0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">Miconia longicuspis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Cogn. in A.DC. &amp; C.DC, Monog. Phan. 7: 850. 1891. (Replaced name)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2FC589BCFD1FA2018E74261DF6009DE2" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" type="comments">
<paragraph id="02C8FD56D0906BB32DD56B18AC30441D" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BBB167116839807E5B2F847243ECC5DA" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">
<taxonomicName id="10E2F196B9FF31773DC9DF47CCB4AC51" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="longicuspis">
<emphasis id="312297EAAD37445CA7265A7C4C842529" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">Miconia longicuspis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Herzog is a later homonym of 
<taxonomicName id="95536C4BCEDF53AA499C4F4935509665" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="longicuspis">
<emphasis id="A1F30DAD3F4C760189A6102A1EEC5AF1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">Miconia longicuspis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Cogn., a treelet from eastern Brazil (
<bibRefCitation id="E81DFE2723793FF7BC2AFF7735532B0A" author="Goldenberg, R" journalOrPublisher="Boletim do Museu de Biologia Mello Leitao - Nova Serie" pageId="1" pageNumber="36" pagination="33 - 58" refId="B3" refString="Goldenberg, R, Reginato, M, 2006. Sinopse da familia Melastomataceae na Estacao Biologica de Santa Lucia (Santa Teresa, Espirito Santo). Boletim do Museu de Biologia Mello Leitao - Nova Serie 20: 33 - 58" title="Sinopse da familia Melastomataceae na Estacao Biologica de Santa Lucia (Santa Teresa, Espirito Santo)." volume="20" year="2006">Goldenberg and Reginato 2006</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="0FEE67927FCDBF3E4FD3406BE054AE7C" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="longicuspidata">
<emphasis id="77B636FABCA6B03E1F7DAF3CF24AEFAF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">Miconia longicuspidata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only from the holotype at Z, a collection by Theodor Herzog (1880-1961) in the mountains of 
<normalizedToken id="9FB20DC2C963119D0C125EF28653168D" originalValue="Cuñucú">Cunucu</normalizedToken>
, Bolivia, in 1907. We have found no isotypes or type photos in G, JE, L, U, W, or WAG. This species most closely matches 
<taxonomicName id="E777C0577B329FE6AAA0C133B7DD974D" authorityName="Markgraf" authorityYear="1927" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="abbreviata">
<emphasis id="3641E30C344EE29889D8C4BB9C673941" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">Miconia abbreviata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Markgr., a widespread shrub that ranges from Bolivia throughout the Amazon basin to the Guianas, but differs in the much denser secondary venation. In 
<taxonomicName id="BFD1DEB42175F1B14D79FFCE5104C045" authorityName="Markgraf" authorityYear="1927" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="abbreviata">
<emphasis id="1033AB2299B2DA098E9A234B04E3582A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">Miconia abbreviata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the secondaries are spaced at about 0.5-0.7 mm apart, in 
<taxonomicName id="9DCED4756E3A24E808D9FE2DE2C81419" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="longicuspidata">
<emphasis id="51777F2F0775DCA14F1B47AA8A042F5D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">Miconia longicuspidata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, only 2-3 mm apart. Theodor Herzog was an expert mountaineer and collector, who explored widely in Bolivia. During his two expeditions to that country in 1907/08 and 1910/11, he collected about 600 species of vascular plants. In 1910, Herzog not only explored the Cordillera Santa Cruz, where 
<taxonomicName id="B7452F24938789D83BEE88D15212CFF0" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="longicuspidata">
<emphasis id="A847E6304B8BE590C077760ADF0A08A6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">Miconia longicuspidata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appears to be endemic, but also surveyed the Cordillera de Cocapata, a range of peaks near Cochabamba extending northwest for about 100 kilometers. A description of the flora of the Cordillera de Santa Cruz is given in 
<bibRefCitation id="154DE8514085EDA663329BFC9077B9C4" author="Herzog, T" journalOrPublisher="Botanische Jahrbuecher fuer Systematik, Pflanzengeschichte und Pflanzengeographie" pageId="1" pageNumber="36" pagination="346 - 405" refId="B4" refString="Herzog, T, 1910. Pflanzenformationen Ostbolivias. Botanische Jahrbuecher fuer Systematik, Pflanzengeschichte und Pflanzengeographie 44: 346 - 405" title="Pflanzenformationen Ostbolivias." volume="44" year="1910">Herzog (1910)</bibRefCitation>
. A color photograph of the type is available at http://www.zuerich-herbarien.uzh.ch.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
